INSERT INTO `article_translation` VALUES (1,'Embedded System','The project was to view the PPP frames exchanged during the use of this connection between a client and a server','## What\'s Sciopta?\r\n\r\nThe Sciopta company is based in Weil em Rhein, Germany and is specialized in embedded computing.\r\nFor 18 months they developed a real-time embedded operating system named SCIOPTA, which is composed of a basic real-time kernel and libraries implementing a network protocol stack.\r\nThis operating system, version 1.0.0, is intended eventually to work on different targets and particularly on X86 cards.\r\n\r\nThe features of this operating system are:\r\n\r\n- Graphical configuration of the application\r\n- Real time system\r\n- The application can fit on a floppy and then be flashed\r\n\r\nThe physical environment of the target board is then reduced to a motherboard, a serial port and an Ethernet port. Current networks implement sockets either by Ethernet or PPP connection.\r\n\r\n## PPP frames visualization project\r\n\r\nThe project target is to view the PPP frames exchanged during the use of this connection between a client and a server. \r\n\r\nThe project is designed under Windows, but the core application files are compiled by a cross-compiler, which is available on Linux. Because of this constraint, we use a Linux emulator, Cygwin, which allowed us to take advantage of the Windows environment.\r\n\r\nThe small size of the nucleus SCIOPTA can run on a floppy disk booting through grub, but we have prefered to  use always the same disk for the two demonstrations by downloading the necessary files with grub via the TFTP protocol.\r\n',1,'en','2010-08-27 15:20:56','2010-09-26 10:01:02',6),(2,'photozama','I completely designed and made this application during a period of three months in Madagascar for the NGO [Vozama](http://www.vozama.org \"Vozama - Sauvons les enfants malgache\").\r\nThe goal is to manage a library of tens of thousands photos.','I completely designed and made this application during a period of three months in Madagascar for the NGO Vozama.\r\nThe goal is to manage a library of tens of thousands photos.\r\n\r\n## The NGO VOZAMA\r\n\r\nVOZAMA is an NGO which has 4 main objectives:\r\n\r\n- teach children not attending school and put them in the rails of a 2 years public or private school period.\r\n- monitor them until the end of primary school (4 years)\r\n- educate parents about the importance of education, their involvement is the key to success\r\n- train these adults to become involved in their development\r\n\r\n## Photozama description \r\n\r\nThe purpose of this application is to order photos, by using a database.\r\nThe application is coded in VB6 and Access.\r\n\r\nSeveral criteria have been set for their organizations:\r\n\r\n- Name\r\n- Theme\r\n- Date\r\n- Photographer (name, function)\r\n- Location (area, position)\r\n- Keywords\r\n\r\nIn addition, an email management has been added at the request of my supervisor, it\'s used to search photos already sent to an address or otherwise know which photo was not sent to that person.\r\nA history of all messages is available with an Excel list  of email already used.\r\n\r\nThe adding process was designed to be as efficient as possible, a first menu to select photos from different folders. When adding multiple information required for the previous picture are automatically enrolled in the next record, allowing a quick way to process similar photos.\r\n\r\nPhotos may also undergo treatment such as adjusting contrast, brightness, resizing, compression or rotation directly in the adding or editing action.',1,'en','2010-08-27 15:27:13','2010-09-24 12:17:26',10),(3,'Attac media library','The project aims to create a website offering a common library, allowing ATTAC association members to exchange their documents (books, DVDs, VHS, articles, CD, CD-ROM).','## Target\r\n\r\nThe project aims to create a website offering a common library, allowing ATTAC association members to exchange their documents (books, DVDs, VHS, articles, CD, CD-ROM).\r\n\r\n## Technologies\r\n\r\n- made with the LAMP technology.\r\n- XML parser and XSL transformer (Sablotron Parser) was used to display the contents of the library.\r\n- native javascript AJAX was used for the library search engine with content indexation (in 2005, js libraries was almost nonexistent)\r\n- CMS SPIP 1.8.2 has been added to allow content management for administrators. They can add articles and menus',1,'en','2010-08-27 15:29:44','2010-09-25 04:12:45',5),(4,'Intracom 2007','Simple project developed with a custom MVC pattern coded in PHP5 OOP','**Site created as a part of HETIC projects**\r\n\r\nI take part to the project as developer, the main functions that I brought to the back office are:\r\n\r\n- user management with specific workflows\r\n- site content management in two languages\r\n- files management (upload, linking,...)\r\n- partner logo pre-processing by using relative relative the GD2 library \r\n\r\nI had developed a custom MVC pattern in PHP Object-oriented for our simple content management needs.',1,'en','2010-08-27 15:32:17','2010-09-24 12:25:22',7),(5,'Kultura','The project is therefore, an artist area in \"MySpace\" style with management of videos, music, photos and another part containing the Kultura activities: organize Latin culture evenings.','**Site created as a part of HETIC projects**\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nKultura was my first experience as a project manager.\r\n\r\nThe project is therefore, it\'s a \"MySpace\" like:<br />\r\n\r\n- artist area with videos, music, photos \r\n- subsribe / profil management interface for artists\r\n- a part containing the Kultura activities: latin parties, danse course, cooking course,...\r\n- a backoffice dedicated to administation tasks\r\n\r\n## Technologies\r\n\r\n- LAMP Environment, using the Code Igniter framework\r\n- javascript: prototype, script.acu.lous, YUI libraries\r\n- use of version control (SVN) to facilitate teamwork\r\n- movies are stored on youtube by using the API, images and music are stored on the server\r\n- SEO optimization with url rewriting, generated sitemaps and a semantic HTML code (XHTML Strict)',1,'en','2010-08-27 15:34:17','2010-09-21 13:21:20',14),(6,'Short film','We have two weeks to write the script, get familiar with the equipment, shooting and editing the film.','**Film made within HETIC videos weeks**\r\nWe have two weeks to write the script, get familiar with the equipment, shooting and editing the film.\r\n\r\nThe shooting has not been easy: Permissions not always granted, freezing cold when our actor was playing outside in shorts  at -5°C and coordination with the other team!\r\nBesides the deal was simple, I\'m an actor for the other team and one of their members is an actor for us...\r\nA nice collaboration but also many difficults, our player was their director!\r\n\r\n<div class=\"videos\">\r\n<object width=\"480\" height=\"331\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.dailymotion.com/swf/video/x1vcd6_timeisrunningout_creation?additionalInfos=0\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowScriptAccess\" value=\"always\"></param><embed type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" src=\"http://www.dailymotion.com/swf/video/x1vcd6_timeisrunningout_creation?additionalInfos=0\" width=\"480\" height=\"331\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\"></embed></object>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n**Credits:**\r\n\r\n- Yohann Ulreich: Director\r\n- Julien Ravat: Editor\r\n- Nathaniel North Cameraman\r\n- Michael Meyer Sound\r\n\r\n**Summary:**\r\nA guy is lost in a time loop, a routine is installed in his life...',1,'en','2010-08-27 15:36:10','2010-09-21 12:58:39',10),(21,'CURSUS','nothing','',1,'en','2010-09-02 15:48:41','2010-09-02 17:00:19',2),(22,'2002 - 2004 | Jean Mermoz High School | Saint-Louis, Alsace, France','Industrial Computing [BTS] (equivalent to [BTEC Higher National] Diploma)','This formation provide the basic knowledge of industrial data processing, a branch of applied computer science that covers the area of design and programming of computerized systems which are not computers as such — often referred to as embedded systems (PLCs, automated systems, intelligent instruments, etc).\r\n\r\nSkills:\r\n\r\n- System architecture\r\n- Assembly, C/C++\r\n- Languages theory\r\n- Software engineering\r\n- Network protocols\r\n',1,'en','2010-09-02 16:55:51','2010-09-11 08:20:21',4),(23,'2004 - 2005 | University Institutes for Technology  | Chalon-sur-Saône, Bourgogne, France','[Professional bachelor]\'s degree in image, sound and techniques activities ','This professional bachelor\'s degree, created in the city of Niepce, the inventor of photography in 1824, aims to train professionals whose expertise in creating multimedia. It\r\nmay include paper (brochure, poster), audio-visual media (CD ROMs, DVDs) or via Internet (website).\r\n\r\nStudents learn to aware of theoretical and cultural context (psychoacoustics, film analysis, principle of digitization, project management, media law, etc.) et handle media techniques (shooting, framing, sound, editing, multimedia integration, etc..).\r\n\r\nThree teaching units structured training:\r\n\r\n- General training\r\n- Tools of design and multimedia creation\r\n- Multimedia applications',1,'en','2010-09-03 16:16:55','2010-09-29 12:12:32',6),(24,'2006 - 2008|<a href=\"http://www.hetic.net\">HETIC : Advanced Studies of Information Technologies and Communication</a>| ','[Master’s Degree] in Engineering and Management of Digital Communication | [Academic Degree] in Multimedia and Communication for the Company','### Information technology\r\nCovering the fundamentals of the Internet, Web static and dynamic multimedia applications, multichannel delivery and multichannel broadcasting.\r\n\r\n### Communication and Multimedia Design\r\nRegarding the processing and analysis of information, mass media, marketing communication, corporate communication, hypertext and the Semantic Web, argumentation, graphics software, design, usability and navigation, design and drafting.\r\n\r\n### Business and Management\r\nRegarding the management and business economics, marketing, operational and strategic marketing, financial analysis, business simulation, business strategy, ICT law, real case studies, scenario planning, business plans, venture capital, web analytics, web marketing, e-transformation, project management.\r\n',1,'en','2010-09-03 17:23:53','2010-09-22 10:40:14',8),(25,'BLOG','blog articles','',1,'en','2010-09-16 10:46:09','2010-09-16 10:46:09',1),(26,'avoid old browsers','All web developer have problems with old browser, we spend to much time to solve old browser mystical bugs... Maybe as youtube or facebook you want to display a notice for users who has an old browser.\r\n\r\nI made a unique js file who must be include at the end of your website. He do all the work for you and display a popup at the top of you webpage.\r\n','## a simple solution to avoid old browsers\r\n\r\nAll web developer have problems with old browser, we spend to much time to solve old browser mystical bugs... Maybe as youtube or facebook you want to display a notice for users who has an old browser. \r\n\r\nI made a unique js file who must be include at the end of your website. He do all the work for you and display a popup at the top of you webpage.\r\n\r\nThis webpage use the lib, try to change your user-agent to see the popup with firefox and the module [User-Agent Switcher](https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/59/).\r\n\r\n### Advantages\r\n\r\n*   write in native javascript, no conflicts with other js libs\r\n*   a simple javascript file to include, nothing to install or upload\r\n*   use a cookie to show the popup only one time\r\n\r\n## The simplest way \r\n\r\njust put this code at the end of your webpage (just before closing body tag):\r\n<pre name=\"code\" class=\"html\"><script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://zazabe.ismerging.us/browser-warning/browser-warning.min.js\"></script></pre>\r\nuncompressed source: <http://zazabe.ismerging.us/browser-warning/browser-warning.auto.js> \r\n## Customize the detection\r\n\r\nI make a **browserWarning** class in native javascript who try to detect the browser version and launch a callback method if the browser is too old. \r\n\r\n### Methods\r\n\r\n**constructor - browserWarning(options)**\r\n\r\noptions: js object  \r\noptions by default, you can change one or more attribute by passing a js object at browserWarning instantiation \r\n\r\n<pre name=\"code\" class=\"js\">{\r\n  // browser version need to be greater than this values\r\n  lowerVersionFor: {\r\n    ie      : 8, \r\n    safari  : 4, \r\n    opera   : 9.5,\r\n    firefox : 3, \r\n    chrome  : 3\r\n  },\r\n  oldByDefault: false, //default detection status\r\n  cookie: {\r\n    enabled: true,\r\n    name:    \'browserWarning\',\r\n    value:   \'allreadyWarned\',\r\n  expired: null\r\n  }\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n**browserWarning.test(callback)**\r\n\r\ncallback: function  \r\ntest if the browser is old and call the callback method in this case. \r\n\r\n### Example\r\n\r\n<pre name=\"code\" class=\"js\">var badBrowser = new browserWarning({\r\n  lowerVersionFor: {\r\n    ie: 7,\r\n    firefox: 2\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n    	\r\nwindow.onload = function(){\r\n  badBrowser.test(function(){\r\n    alert(\'your browser is too old !\');\r\n  });\r\n}</pre>    	\r\n    \r\n\r\n### source code\r\n\r\n<http://zazabe.ismerging.us/browser-warning/browser-warning.class.js> \r\n## Used sources \r\n\r\nI use many different sources to make this class: \r\n\r\n*   [team-noir](http://blog.team-noir.net/2009/06/fight-old-browsers-warning-with-jquery/): I reuse the cookie principe\r\n*   [jQuery library](http://jquery.com/): I extract the expand method to allow my class to merge to js object (useful for constructor options)\r\n*   [Peter-Paul Koch\'s browser detection code](http://www.quirksmode.org/js/detect.html)\r\n',1,'en','2010-09-16 12:05:56','2010-09-28 10:54:10',11),(27,'2007 - 2010 | <a href=\"http://www.brainsonic.com\">Brainsonic : The RichMedia Factory</a> | Paris, Île-de-France, France','none','### My Brainsonic playground\r\n\r\n**During 3 years, I developed a CMS, based on Symfony,** specialized in medias broadcasting.\r\nI worked by iteration, the first version was designed to delivery content for [set top box](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Set-top_box \"Wikipedia : Set-top box\"). The project was growing fast and some people joined me to improve it. \r\n\r\nWe started to use it for websites with more and more functionalities (UGC video, encoding server, multi-sites, comments, tags, advanced user management like LDAP connection, SEO, cross-platform publication, deported widgets, web services API, CDN and cloud computing support).\r\n\r\nAs the project had more importance, we start to rationalize our process by unit testing, continuous integration and revisions control.\r\n\r\nI am not authorized to speak about customer projects on which I worked but you will find most of this references on Brainsonic website under the heading [WebTV](http://www.brainsonic.com/offres/webtv/ \"Brainsonic WebTV platforms\").\r\n\r\nI worked punctually on other projects, based on **Joomla**, **Drupal**, **javascript** (live video broadcasting framework), **Flash** or pure **HTML/CSS integration** jobs...\r\n\r\nI was in charge of our **UNIX system administration** when our sysadmin was in holiday.\r\n\r\n### Brainsonic activites\r\n\r\n- WebTV\r\n- Rich Media\r\n- Videomail\r\n- Video\r\n- CDN\r\n- Streaming\r\n- Live',1,'en','2010-09-18 09:03:03','2010-09-29 12:41:28',19),(28,'CMS for WebTV','\r\nMy main job for Brainsonic:\r\nDesign and develop a CMS specialized in media management.\r\nStarted as a small project it\'s became the most used solution for WebTV creation with a huge functionalities list, all people from the R&D have taken part.\r\n','## At the beginning...\r\n\r\nDuring 3 years, I developed a CMS, based on symfony, specialized in media broadcasting.\r\nI worked by iteration, first version was designed to delivery content for set top box. \r\n\r\n## The CMS reborned\r\n\r\nThen, I developed our CMS core with default functionalities: multi-sites logic with plugins management system who allow super-admin to enable/disable them for each site.\r\nA default webTV with common functionalities (videos, user management, comments, tags, categorization) was instantiated in less than 1 hour. (without client side development).\r\n\r\nThe project was growing fast and other people joined me to improve it.\r\n\r\n**Some features:**\r\n\r\n- advanced user management (LDAP support, custom workflow, front profils)\r\n- SEO content optimization\r\n- support of our custom encoding server based on C and PHP\r\n- cross-platform content and media publication (youtube, dailymotion,...)\r\n- deported video widgets\r\n- web services API with a generated online interface for demonstration/documentation\r\n- CDN and cloud computing support\r\n- custom front-side JS framework using jQuery with server-side binding. (symfony routing and widgets recognition).\r\n\r\nDifficulties came when we had more than 20 multi-sites in production, we started to rationalize our process by using unit test, continuous integration and revision control.',1,'en','2010-09-18 11:05:14','2010-09-26 10:11:48',10),(29,'jQuery','jQuery / Javascript projects','',1,'en','2010-09-21 08:53:52','2010-09-21 08:54:28',2),(30,'FFSA.tv','This WebTV was created to provide media to automobile sport fans.\r\nWith categorized and tagged media, user can found the content they like, if they have subscribe to the FFSA Club the content is automatically profiled according to their wishes.','## French federation of Automobile Sport WebTV\r\n\r\nThis WebTV was created to provide media to automobile sport fans.\r\nWith categorized and tagged media, user can found the content they like, if they have subscribe to the FFSA Club the content is automatically profiled according to their wishes.\r\nLogged users can rate and comment more than a thousand of medias classified in one huge catalog.\r\n\r\n## My participation\r\n\r\nI done all the HTML/CSS integration and I used our CMS to dynamize the content. Subscribe and login part was allready developped by a friend in the previous version of the WebTV.\r\n\r\n**Features:**\r\n\r\n- categorization\r\n- tagging\r\n- comments\r\n- rating\r\n- user profiled content\r\n- subsribe/login interface synchronized with existing FFSA.fr database\r\n\r\n**<a href=\"http://www.ffsa.tv/\" title=\"FFSA.tv WebTV\" target=\"mmeyer_sites\">FFSA.tv</a>**',0,'en','2010-09-22 10:57:29','2010-09-29 17:25:18',13),(31,'Cité des Sciences','We have developed two WebTV for providing an attractive content , they use the same multi-site backoffice to manage the content (the CMS for WebTV). ','## The Cité des Sciences et de l\'Industrie\r\n\r\nThe Cité des Sciences et de l\'Industrie is the biggest science museum in Europe. It is a public establishment of an industrial and commercial character specializing in the fostering of scientific and technical culture. Created on the initiative of President Giscard d\'Estaing, its goal is to spread scientific and technical knowledge among the public, particularly for youth, and for creating public interest in science, research, and industry.\r\n**[source: wikipedia](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cité_des_Sciences_et_de_l\'Industrie \"Cité des Sciences et de l\'Industrie\")**\r\n\r\nWe have developed two WebTV for providing an attractive content , they use the same multi-site backoffice to manage the content (the CMS for WebTV).\r\n\r\n## Media magazines\r\n\r\nI had developed a custom interface in our CMS to manage weekly magazine. Each week, 20 new medias are published in a magazine, the magazines are accessible for five weeks, after the content is synchronized with the VOD platform.\r\nThe interface is simple and easy to use, giving the best user experience with a quick contents access.\r\nWe used a new communication technique with our flash player, the player request all by our server side webservice API.\r\nI had developed the API with a generated documentation and a test interface.\r\n\r\n## The VOD WebTV\r\n\r\nIt\'s a classic webtv with all needed features: categorization, tagging, comments, rating, subscribe/login.\r\n \r\n\r\n- **[universcience.tv](http://www.universcience.tv \"universcience.tv la Web TV scientifique\")**\r\n- **[universcience-vod.fr](http://www.universcience-vod.fr \"universcience VOD - La plate-forme vidéo des sciences et des techniques\")**',0,'en','2010-09-22 11:42:30','2010-09-29 17:25:18',9),(32,'Les Echos Group','The CMS allowed a global management system for seven WebTV, with cross-platform publication support (media can be exchanged with each webTV) and a custom newsletter generator.','## Les Echos Group\r\nLes Échos is the first daily French financial newspaper, formerly owned by the British media group Pearson PLC, and sold in 2007 to the French luxury goods conglomerate LVMH. It was created in 1908 by the brothers Robert and Emile Servan-Schreiber and became a daily newspaper in 1928. It has a web site (http://www.lesechos.fr) and several blogs. The newspaper was bought by Pearson in 1988.\r\n**[source: wikipedia](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Les_%C3%89chos_%28France%29 \"Les Échos (France)\")**\r\n\r\n## multi-site WebTV\r\n\r\nIt\'s one of the first WebTV using the CMS, I developed the multi-site support for this project.\r\n\r\nI have also developed all plugins who became the standard for all WebTV, categorization, tagging, comments, rating, playlist and user management.\r\nSome of this plugins was based on plugin coming from the symfony community but the most of the time we had to customize them.\r\n\r\nThe CMS allowed a global management system for seven WebTV, with cross-platform publication support (media can be exchanged with each webTV) and a custom newsletter generator.\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n- **[Les Echos Group WebTV Portal](http://www.groupe-lesechos.tv/ \"Portail WebTv Groupe Les Echos\")**\r\n- **[Les Echos](http://www.lesechostv.fr/ \"Les Echos WebTV\")**\r\n- **[Salon des entrepreneurs](http://www.salondesentrepreneurs.tv/ \"Salon des entrepreneurs WebTV\")**\r\n- **[Investir](http://www.investir.tv/ \"Investir WebTV\")**\r\n- **[Connaissance des arts](http://www.connaissancedesarts.tv/ \"Connaissance des arts WebTV\")**\r\n- **[Radio classique](http://www.radioclassique.tv/ \"Radio classique WebTV\")**\r\n\r\n',0,'en','2010-09-22 12:24:29','2010-09-29 17:25:18',9),(33,'Ineum Consulting','The company needs was a single platform to manage multilingual websites. We have provided a Joomla based solution, with customized plugins allowing cross-websites articles publication.','## Description\r\n\r\nIneum Consulting is a management consulting company based in France that specializes in corporate strategy, organization, and information systems issues.\r\n\r\nIneum was formed as a spin off from Deloitte France\'s consulting division; its headquarters are still in Paris. The firm now has approximately 1,300 employees in Algeria, Australia, France, Belgium, Morocco, Luxembourg, the Netherlands, Switzerland, United Kingdom and the United States.\r\n\r\n**[source: wikipedia](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ineum_Consulting \"Ineum Consulting\")**\r\n\r\n## Internationalized websites\r\n\r\nThe company needs was a single platform to manage multilingual websites. We have provided a Joomla based solution, with customized plugins allowing cross-websites articles publication.\r\nI worked occasionally on this project, for maintenance and debugging, when the main developer had quit our company.\r\n\r\n- **[Ineum Consulting](http://www.ineumconsulting.com/ \"Ineum Consulting website\")** ',0,'en','2010-09-22 13:14:51','2010-09-29 17:25:18',8),(34,'qBox plugin : sliding boxes','Used to display some boxes in a define area, others will come from outside with a sliding effects. \r\nFull customizable, this plugin can be used in many situation. (photo gallery, articles random list, ...).','## Description\r\nUsed to display some boxes in an area, others will come from outside with a sliding effects. \r\nFull customizable, this plugin can be used in many situation. (photo gallery, articles random list, ...).\r\n\r\nCurrently tested on **Firefox 3.6**, **IE8** and **Opera**. \r\nThere\'s a bug on Chrome, seem to come from outerWidth(true) jQuery method who return a wrong value.\r\n  \r\n## Examples:\r\n\r\n\r\n### default 3x3 qBox, using 12 li boxes\r\n\r\n- [demo](@ajax_article?id=35)\r\n- [source](@ajax_article?id=36)\r\n\r\n### 3x1 qBox, using 5 a>img boxes, sliding from the top and starting by the last position\r\n\r\n- [demo](@ajax_article?id=37)\r\n- [source](@ajax_article?id=38)\r\n\r\n### [invasion qBox demo 25x25 boxes](http://www.michel-meyer.fr/qbox-invasion.php \"qBox jQuery plugin : invasion demo\") \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Download\r\n\r\n[git repository](http://github.com/zazabe/qbox \"qbox\'s github page\") \r\n<pre class=\"brush: shell\">\r\ngit clone git://github.com/zazabe/qbox.git\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n## Instantiation\r\n\r\nSome CSS is required, defining box area and boxes size.\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"brush: css\">#area {\r\n  width: 450px;\r\n  height: 450px;\r\n  position: relative;\r\n  overflow: hidden;\r\n}\r\n#area .box {\r\n  width: 150px;\r\n  height: 150px;\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nqBox instantiation with default parameters\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"brush: js\">$(\'#box\').qbox();</pre>\r\n\r\n## Options\r\n\r\n<pre  class=\"brush: js\">$(\'#box\').qbox({\r\nslide: {\r\n    effect:    \'linear\',\r\n    duration:  500,\r\n    from:      \'all\',     // sliding direction => all, top, right, bottom or left\r\n    by:        \'random\',  // sliding position order => random, asc or desc \r\n    custom:     null      // custom slide position function \r\n                          // => function(){//this = qbox instance} (override slide.by)\r\n},                         \r\nbox: {\r\n    selector: \'li\',       // box jQuery selector\r\n    rows:     3,          // row number\r\n    cols:     3           // col number\r\n},\r\nqtime: {\r\n    interval: 2,          // step number before sliding\r\n    step:     1000,       // step duration in ms\r\n    running:  true        // sliding is running by default\r\n}\r\n});\r\n</pre>\r\n',1,'en','2010-09-27 08:35:06','2010-09-30 10:28:00',37),(35,'qbox example1 : demo','javascripts: \r\n  - /themeZazabe2/js/qbox-examples.js\r\nstylesheets:\r\n  - /themeZazabe2/css/qbox-examples.css','<style type=\"text/css\">\r\n#example1 {\r\n  width: 340px;\r\n  height: 340px;\r\n  position: relative;\r\n  overflow: hidden;\r\n\r\n  border: 2px solid #aaa;\r\n  margin: 20px auto;\r\n}\r\n\r\nbody.article #main #example1 ul li {\r\n  width: 78px;\r\n  height: 78px;\r\n\r\n  margin: 10px;\r\n  border-style: solid;\r\n  border-width: 8px;\r\n  -webkit-border-radius: 10px;\r\n  -moz-border-radius: 10px;\r\n  border-radius: 10px;\r\n\r\n  text-align: center;\r\n  line-height: 75px;\r\n  float: left;\r\n  list-style: none;\r\n  padding: 0;\r\n  background: none;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#example1 li p {\r\n	font-size: 2em;\r\n	font-weight: bolder;\r\n	text-transform:capitalize;\r\n}\r\n</style>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"example1\">\r\n   <ul>\r\n	<li><p>box1</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>box2</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>box3</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>box4</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>box5</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>box6</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>box7</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>box8</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>box9</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>box10</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>box11</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>box12</p></li>\r\n   </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n',0,'en','2010-09-27 10:00:56','2010-09-27 16:35:41',12),(36,'qbox example1 : source','javascripts:\r\n  - /themeZazabe2/syntax-highlighter/scripts/shBrushXml.js\r\n  - /themeZazabe2/js/qbox-examples.js\r\n','html:\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"brush: html\">  <div id=\"example1\">\r\n   <ul>\r\n    <li><p>box1</p></li>\r\n    <li><p>box2</p></li>\r\n    <li><p>box3</p></li>\r\n    <li><p>box4</p></li>\r\n    <li><p>box5</p></li>\r\n    <li><p>box6</p></li>\r\n    <li><p>box7</p></li>\r\n    <li><p>box8</p></li>\r\n    <li><p>box9</p></li>\r\n    <li><p>box10</p></li>\r\n    <li><p>box11</p></li>\r\n    <li><p>box12</p></li>\r\n   </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nstyle: \r\n\r\n<pre class=\"brush: css\">#example1 {\r\n  width: 340px;\r\n  height: 340px;\r\n  position: relative;\r\n  overflow: hidden;\r\n}\r\n#example1 li {\r\n  width: 78px;\r\n  height: 78px;\r\n  margin: 10px;\r\n  border-style: solid;\r\n  border-width: 8px;\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\njavascript:\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"brush: js\">$(document).ready(function(){\r\n  $(\'#example1\').qbox();\r\n});\r\n</pre>',0,'en','2010-09-27 10:02:52','2010-09-27 16:29:00',14),(37,'qbox example2 - demo','javascripts:\r\n  - /themeZazabe2/js/qbox-examples.js','<style type=\"text/css\">\r\n#example2 {\r\n  width: 510px;\r\n  height: 120px;\r\n  overflow: hidden;\r\n  position: relative;\r\n  border: 1px solid #999;\r\n  margin: 10px auto;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#example2 a {\r\n  display: block;\r\n  width: 150px;\r\n  height: 100px;\r\n  margin: 10px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#example2 a img {\r\n  border: none;\r\n}\r\n\r\n</style>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"example2\">\r\n##mediaList##\r\n</div>',0,'en','2010-09-27 17:06:49','2010-09-27 17:33:59',4),(38,'qbox example2 : source','javascripts:\r\n  - /themeZazabe2/js/qbox-examples.js','html:\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"brush: html\">&lt;div id=\"example2\"&gt;\r\n    &lt;a href=\"image1.jpg\"&gt;&lt;img src=\"image1-small.jpg\" &gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n    &lt;a href=\"image2.jpg\"&gt;&lt;img src=\"image2-small.jpg\" &gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n    &lt;a href=\"image3.jpg\"&gt;&lt;img src=\"image3-small.jpg\" &gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n    &lt;a href=\"image4.jpg\"&gt;&lt;img src=\"image4-small.jpg\" &gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n    &lt;a href=\"image5.jpg\"&gt;&lt;img src=\"image5-small.jpg\" &gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;</pre>\r\n\r\njavascript:\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"brush: js\">$(\'#example2\').qbox({\r\n    slide: {\r\n        effect: \'easeInElastic\',  // available only with jquery-ui\r\n        duration: 2000,\r\n        from: \'top\',\r\n        by: \'desc\'\r\n    },\r\n    box: {\r\n        selector: \'a\', //box jQuery selector\r\n        rows: 1, //number of row\r\n        cols: 3 //number by row\r\n    },\r\n    qtime: {\r\n        interval: 3,\r\n        step: 1000\r\n    }\r\n});</pre>\r\n\r\nstyle:\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"brush: css\">#example2 {\r\n  width: 510px;\r\n  height: 120px;\r\n  overflow: hidden;\r\n  position: relative;\r\n  border: 1px solid #999;\r\n  margin: 10px auto;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#example2 a {\r\n  display: block;\r\n  width: 150px;\r\n  height: 100px;\r\n  margin: 10px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#example2 a img {\r\n  border: none;\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n',0,'en','2010-09-27 17:19:18','2010-09-27 17:42:30',2),(39,'Be Inside : 360 video','During 6 mouths we prepared our project based on 360° video captured by the ladybug camera. It\'s the same technology that Google used for Google Streetview application.\r\n','## The project\r\n\r\nTo validate our academic degree in communication, we had to present an innovative project to business angels.\r\n\r\nWe was a team of 5 peoples, \r\n- CHANTELOUP Sabrina : project manager\r\n- DIALLO Dieynabou : Head of Communications\r\n- MEYER Michel : Head of R&D\r\n- RIBEIRO Amandine : Marketing Manager\r\n- ULREICH Yohann : Financial Officer	\r\n\r\nDuring 6 mouths we prepared our project based on 360° video captured by the ladybug camera. It\'s the same technology that Google used for Google Streetview application.\r\n\r\nThe 360° interactive video brings a new dimension to the video on the Internet: immersion. Much more realistic than just virtual tours, 360° videos are achieved by digital HD cameras. Composed of several cameras, the system records video from different angles. Then, our 360 video player allow users to interact with the video.\r\n\r\n## Interactivity\r\n\r\nI developed an Adobe AIR application to generate an XML dedicated to our 360 video player. The XML describe interactive shape presented in the 360 video player.\r\n\r\n## Business plan\r\n\r\nWe produce a business plan to validate and persuade investors that\'s our project is viable.\r\n\r\n## Demonstration\r\n\r\n<iframe style=\"height: 370px; width: 540px;overflow:hidden;border:none;\" src=\"http://www.michel-meyer.fr/demonstration/index.html\"></iframe>\r\n',1,'en','2010-09-28 12:31:41','2010-09-28 12:45:30',3);
